                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-03-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 694.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise the return to San
                    Salvador on February 16 of President Begalado after a brief visit to Guatemala
                    City. * * * I am also informed from Managua that the President of Guatemala has
                    joined in the arbitration treaty signed at the Corinto conference on January 20,
                    1902, by the Presidents of Nicaragua, Costa Rica, Salvador, and Honduras, in
                    accordance with his promise to President Iglesias. * * * The peace of Central
                    America now appears assured in the near future. * * *</p>
                <p>With assurances, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Lawrence Merry.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
